    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-06-01T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-06-01T03:00:00-05:00" n="884"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d884">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/320: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-01T17:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 1, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 1—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>142. Department’s 73, May 27, 6 p.m. Under date of May 29 the oil companies
                    received from the Foreign Office a fairly satisfactory <pb facs="0741" n="733"
                        xml:id="pg_733"/> reply in the form of an <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi> in regard to the Korean oil quota problem and have
                    referred the reply to their principals for consideration. Under the
                    circumstances the Embassy does not consider it necessary at the present juncture
                    to take action under the Department’s authorization. The Standard interests
                    concur in this view.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
